            // because keeping it would place it at index 'fixed_points', and since 
            // nums[i] != fixed_points, it wouldn't be a fixed point at this position.
            // Since we want the maximum, skipping it is the best local choice
            // to preserve the possibility of finding an element later that *does* equal 'fixed_points'.
        }

        return fixed_points;
    }
};
